*/This version of the solver is used to run multiple configurations given an fzn instance. 

This folder is used for the flatzinc interface. The solver requires the boost library. Download the latest version https://www.boost.org into the main solver folder.

*/You first need to compile the code with:

$ make

This will generate the executable file fzn-mistral in the 'bin' folder.

*/ You can test a flatzinc instance with

$./mistral-fz  --time_limit 6    --print_sta  benchmark/fzn-mono1.fzn

The option '--timelimit $v' is used to specify the time limit and the option '--print_sta' is used to print the statistics


*/ Use the following to generate an fzn file "flattened.fzn" given an mzn model "f.mzn" and a dzn data "d.mzn" 

$minizinc --compile --solver org.minizinc.mzn-fzn -I mznlib/ f.mzn d.dzn --fzn flattened.fzn 

For instance: 
$minizinc --compile --solver org.minizinc.mzn-fzn -I mznlib/ benchmark/atsp.mzn benchmark/atsp-instance5_0p15.dzn --fzn benchmark/use-mznlib.fzn 
